Name: Sincock, Miss. Maude
Remarks: During the evacuation, she was one of the last to board the lifeboat

Name: Dean, Miss. Elizabeth Gladys 'Millvina'
Remarks: youngest passenger, last survivor to die of old age

Name: Dean, Master. Bertram Vere
Remarks: became friends with George William Beauchamp, married daughter of a shopowner, shop previously owned by Henry Price Hodges

Name: Heikkinen, Miss. Laina
Remarks: She was most likely transferred to boat 10 because she can remember that she stayed in the boat for about 6 hours before help arrived, apparently waited for 6 hours until Carpathia rescue, transferred from 14 to 10.

Name: Marvin, Mrs. Mary Graham Carmichael
Remarks: initially in boat 14 then transferred to 10

Name: Lundin, Miss. Olga Elida
Profession: her account could suggest boat 15 and 13, but her fiance was not allowed on the boat, so it must have been a boat more strictly supervised and it left relatively early. boat 10 seems more likely, as it encountered bodies and debris later, had mostly women on board and left earlier.
